If I was going to start from scratch with proxmox 9 build with 

Synology 
Create Media Share
Control Panel > Shared Folder
Create > Create Shared Folder

Name: 
Description:
Location: Volume : Btrfs
Uncheck Enable Recycle Bin

File Services
Enable NFS service
Maximum NFS protocol: NFSv4.1

Enabling NFS on the Shared folder
    Edit Shared folder
        Select NFS Permissions
            Create 
                Hostname or IP:
                Privilege: Read/White
                Squash: No mapping
                Security sys
            Check Enable asynchronous
            Check Allow users to access mount subfolders
            Save


Proxmox
apt-get install nala -y
nala update && nala upgrade -y
nala install nfs-kernel-server cifs-utils -y
systemctl start nfs-kernel-server
systemctl enable nfs-kernel-server

bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/community-scripts/ProxmoxVE/main/tools/pve/post-pve-install.sh)"
bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/community-scripts/ProxmoxVE/main/tools/pve/cron-update-lxcs.sh)"


Add existing drive to inventory
Host > Disks > Select Disk > Wipe Disk > Initialize Disk with GPT > xfs format > name storage


mkdir /mnt/pve
